African’s foremost Leadership Academy, ALA celebrated its fourth anniversary on April 12, 2022.The Ausso Leadership Academy mentors business leaders and entrepreneurs to scale their businesses geometrically in order to maximize the jobs they create and enable shared prosperity. On the occasion, an elated Austin Okere, Founder of the Academy stated that “the joy of ALA In her leadership impacts, comes from seeing others achieve more than they thought they were capable of.” Four years ago, the Ausso Leadership Academy was launched to fill the gap in practical and experiential business impact, by helping businesses to set a performance ambition and put in place a system that delivers. Since then, the Ausso Leadership Academy has mentored over 250 Delegates from about 50 Businesses and impacted over 1,500 attendees across Africa. “Today is yet another opportunity to deeply appreciate you for your custom and your continued confidence in us. Thanks to our partners, customers, champions, and faculty who have made this dream come true.” Okere continued. Austin Okere, Founder of ALA is also an Entrepreneur-in-Residence at Columbia Business School, New York. He was appointed to the Advisory Board of the Global Business School Network (GBSN) in Washington DC in recognition of his contribution to the development of business education and knowledge transfer in Africa. Austin has facilitated at the United States International University (USIU) in Kenya and has served as a Consultant to the Sustainable Development Goals, African Center (SDGCA) in Rwanda. Austin served as a member of the World Economic Forum’s (WEF) Global Agenda Council and was listed on the United Kingdom’s C.Hub Magazine 100 Most Influential Creatives in 2016. After retiring from CWG Plc, the company which he founded and the largest security in the technology sector of the Nigerian Stock Exchange, Austin Okere set up the Ausso Leadership Academy (ALA) in pursuance of his vision of Shared Prosperity.